\ val_cmp for matrices: shape-then-elementwise total order.

\ identical matrices are equal
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix = .       \ -1

\ differing element -> not equal
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 5 ] 2 2 matrix = .       \ 0

\ differing shape -> not equal
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix = .   \ 0

\ elementwise ordering
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 5 6 7 8 ] 2 2 matrix lt .       \ -1
[ 5 6 7 8 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix gt .       \ -1

\ shape orders before contents: fewer rows sorts first
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix [ 9 9 9 9 9 9 9 9 9 ] 3 3 matrix lt .   \ -1

\ matrices can live in sets without collapsing (distinct shapes/contents)
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 5 ] 2 2 matrix 2 set size .  \ 2

\ identical matrices dedup in a set
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 2 set size .  \ 1
